'''Nosh''' is the Yiddish Word for [[Snack food]].

As have many Yiddish Words, like [[Chutzpah]], Nosh has been accepted into English and is used to refer to [[Junk Food]] and to [[Nibble]]. It is another example of words which slip into such common usage their origin is long forgotten. Interestingly nosh meaning food (not necessarily junk food) or the act of eating has common usage particularly in London Cockney and in Australian slang, even appearing in slang dictionaries. So either it passed from Yiddish to both Cockney and Australian slang separately, or more probably was in use in London dialects long enough ago to make it's way downunder with the convicts.
